description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Unscheduled Care Division of Aneurin Bevan University Health Board for caring, enthusiastic and motivated individuals. If you are looking for a new challenge this may be the opportunity for you. You will be expected to work as part of the multidisciplinary team and be actively involved in providing high standards of care to acute stroke patients. You will also be expected to demonstrate a high level of nursing assessment and clinical care skills by supporting Band 5 nurses and other Band 2 health care support workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of ABUHB Clinical Futures the Respiratory NIV/High Care Unit will be moving from the Royal Gwent Hospital to the Grange University Hospital in November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a highly motivated, skilled, knowledgeable dynamic individual with excellent caring &amp; communication skills we welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welsh Language Skills need to be learnt when appointed to the post Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 08th October, 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Ward Manager Nicky Marsh on 01633 238971 or alternatively email Nicky.Marsh@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
